A 'Buteo regalis' is a bird of prey commonly known as the Ferruginous Hawk. 
It is a large bird with a wingspan of up to 4 feet. 
Its body is predominantly rusty-brown, with a white underbelly and yellow legs. 
The head is rounded, with a hooked beak and piercing eyes. 
Ferruginous Hawks are found primarily in open grasslands and deserts across North and Central America. 
They are an apex predator in their habitat, feeding on small mammals like rabbits and ground squirrels. 
Their population is threatened by loss of habitat and human-made structures, such as wind turbines.
